-- IBM CFO sees "good momentum" heading into 2007
-- 
-- Thu Jan 18, 2007 4:43pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/01/18/us-ibm-results-outlook-idUSN1818599820070118

 

 SAN FRANCISCO  (Reuters) - International Business Machines Corp. ( IBM.N ) is optimistic about the momentum of its business heading into 2007, the company's chief financial officer said on Thursday. 

 "We feel good about the momentum as we enter 2007," Chief Financial Officer Mark Loughridge told investors on a conference call following IBM's year-end financial report. Wall Street analysts are looking for IBM to report revenue, on average, of $94.48 billion for the full 2007 year, up from the $91.42 billion the company reported during 2006. Earlier the world's largest technology services company posted a fourth-quarter net profit of $3.54 billion, as revenue climbed to $26.3 billion from $24.4 billion a year earlier. (Additional reporting by  Eric Auchard  in San Francisco)